#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 231. Khīrarukkhopamasutta → khīrarukkhena (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.231:0.3"
msgid "231. Khīrarukkhopamasutta"
msgstr "231. The Simile of the Latex-Producing Tree"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.160"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.231:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Yassa kassaci, bhikkhave, bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā cakkhuviññeyyesu "
"rūpesu yo rāgo so atthi, yo doso so atthi, yo moho so atthi, yo rāgo so "
"appahīno, yo doso so appahīno, yo moho so appahīno tassa parittā cepi "
"cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā cakkhussa āpāthaṃ āgacchanti pariyādiyantevassa cittaṃ; "
"ko pana vādo adhimattānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, take any monk or nun who, when it comes to sights known by the "
"eye, still has greed, hate, and delusion, and has not given them up. If even "
"trivial sights come into their range of vision they overcome their mind, not "
"to mention those that are compelling."

msgctxt "sn35.231:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn35.231:1.3"
msgid ""
"Yo, bhikkhave, rāgo, so atthi, yo doso so atthi, yo moho so atthi, yo rāgo "
"so appahīno, yo doso so appahīno, yo moho so appahīno … pe …."
msgstr ""
"Because they still have greed, hate, and delusion, and have not given them "
"up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.231:2.1"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, bhikkhave, bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā jivhāviññeyyesu "
"rasesu yo rāgo so atthi … pe …."
msgstr "When it comes to sounds … smells … tastes … touches …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.231:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, bhikkhave, bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā manoviññeyyesu "
"dhammesu yo rāgo so atthi, yo doso so atthi, yo moho so atthi, yo rāgo so "
"appahīno, yo doso so appahīno, yo moho so appahīno, tassa parittā cepi "
"manoviññeyyā dhammā manassa āpāthaṃ āgacchanti pariyādiyantevassa cittaṃ; ko "
"pana vādo adhimattānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"thoughts known by the mind, they still have greed, hate, and delusion, and "
"have not given them up. If even trivial thoughts come into the range of the "
"mind they overcome their mind, not to mention those that are compelling."

msgctxt "sn35.231:3.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn35.231:3.3"
msgid ""
"Yo, bhikkhave, rāgo, so atthi, yo doso so atthi, yo moho so atthi, yo rāgo "
"so appahīno, yo doso so appahīno, yo moho so appahīno."
msgstr ""
"Because they still have greed, hate, and delusion, and have not given them "
"up."

# BB leaves these untranslated, but they all have well established English names. In addition, the translation “milk-sap” is over-literal. While sap is loosely used of any plant liquid, correctly speaking it is a separate liquid. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sap The milky liquid—which these trees do in fact produce—is called latex. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latex
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.231:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, khīrarukkho assattho vā nigrodho vā pilakkho vā "
"udumbaro vā daharo taruṇo komārako."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a latex-producing tree—such as a bodhi, a banyan, a wavy "
"leaf fig, or a cluster fig—that’s a tender young sapling."

#. VAR: ābhindeyya → bhindeyya (bj-a, s1-3, km) | abhindeyya (katthaci)
msgctxt "sn35.231:4.2"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ puriso tiṇhāya kuṭhāriyā yato yato ābhindeyya āgaccheyya khīran”ti?"
msgstr ""
"If a man were to chop it here and there with a sharp axe, would latex come "
"out?”"

msgctxt "sn35.231:4.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn35.231:4.4"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn35.231:4.5"
msgid "“Yañhi, bhante, khīraṃ taṃ atthī”ti."
msgstr "Because it still has latex.”"

#. </p><p>
