"parittā cepi cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā cakkhussa āpāthaṃ āgacchanti "
"pariyādiyantevassa cittaṃ; ko pana vādo adhimattānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, take any monk or nun who, when it comes to sights known by "
"the eye, still has greed, hate, and delusion, and has not given them up. If "
"even trivial sights come into their range of vision they overcome their "
"mind, not to mention those that are compelling."

msgctxt "sn35.231:5.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

